 :tx/rationale "PSR AUDIT — 3 issues found. (1) PSR-1 uses TF-IDF-like scoring but the spec statements are SHORT (typically 20-50 words). TF-IDF works best on longer documents. For short text, EXACT KEYWORD OVERLAP is more effective than TF-IDF weighting. Simpler: lowercase both texts, split into words, count intersection. Score = |intersection| / sqrt(|input_words| * |spec_words|). This is cosine similarity on bag-of-words — well-understood, fast, works on short text. (2) PSR-2 says 'wire into footer for all text-bearing commands' but the footer is ALREADY complex (M(t), next action, contextual hint). Adding spec references risks OVERLOADING the footer. FIX: Spec references should be on a SEPARATE line, clearly labeled 'Spec:'. And should ONLY appear when relevance score > 0.3 (strong match), not > 0.1 (weak noise). (3) PSR-3 wiring into seed Constraints: seed already has a constraint cap of 5. Adding PSR matches could push total constraints past the cap. FIX: PSR matches should be MERGED with existing constraints by deduplication, not appended. If a PSR match is already in the graph-proximity constraints, skip it. Only ADD genuinely new spec elements that the graph missed."
